  <header class="fade-in">
    <h1>Welcome to Turkana Leo Magazine</h1>
    <p>Promoting Community Development, Technology Empowerment & Cultural Heritage</p>
  </header>
  <section id="about" class="fade-in">
    <h2>About Us</h2>
    <p>Turkana Leo Magazine is a vibrant digital platform rooted in Turkana County. We amplify voices from underserved communities, champion local talents, and foster awareness through innovation and culture.</p>
    <p>We’re driven by the values of inclusivity, digital empowerment, and storytelling — with a strong focus on youth, women, and marginalized groups in our society. Our goal is to support community-led transformation through education, media, and collaborative development.</p>
  </section>
  <section id="projects" class="fade-in">
    <h2>Key Focus Areas</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Community Development:</strong> Promoting sustainable livelihoods, health, education, and environmental conservation.</li>
      <li><strong>Technology Empowerment:</strong> Training and exposing youth to digital tools and coding to prepare them for future careers.</li>
      <li><strong>Women & Girl Empowerment:</strong> Supporting leadership, entrepreneurship, and digital literacy for women and girls.</li>
      <li><strong>Creative Industries:</strong> Highlighting talents in music, art, crafts, design, and storytelling through digital platforms.</li>
      <li><strong>Digital Storytelling:</strong> Sharing authentic stories from Turkana to preserve culture and inspire change.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section id="services" class="fade-in">
    <h2>Our Services</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Web Design & Development:</strong> Creating inclusive websites that serve communities and local businesses.</li>
      <li><strong>Graphic Design:</strong> Visual communication that supports community causes and identity.</li>
      <li><strong>Branding:</strong> Helping small businesses and organizations build authentic, impactful brands.</li>
      <li><strong>Digital Education Facilitation:</strong> Organizing training, mentorship, and access to tools for youth and women.</li>
      <li><strong>Media Coverage & Publishing:</strong> Documenting and distributing stories, events, and campaigns from the grassroots level.</li>
      <li><strong>Community Engagement:</strong> Co-designing programs and dialogues with stakeholders to respond to local needs.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section id="contact" class="fade-in">
